## Answer (1)

The problem is that the server is closing the connection after sending the message.

```
 n = write(newsockfd,message,strlen(message));
 if (n < 0) {
     perror("ERROR writing to socket");
     exit(1);
 }

 close(newsockfd);
 close(sockfd);
```

The client is then trying to read from a closed connection.

```
 n = read(sockfd,buffer,BUFFER_SIZE);
 if (n < 0) {
     perror("ERROR reading from socket");
     exit(1);
 }
```

The client should close the connection after reading the message.

```
 n = read(sockfd,buffer,BUFFER_SIZE);
 if (n < 0) {
     perror("ERROR reading from socket");
     exit(1);
 }

 close(sockfd);
```

