## Answer (0)

If you want to change the space between items only in one list, you can use

```
\begin{itemize}[itemsep=10pt]
```

instead of

```
\begin{itemize}
```

A complete example:

```
\documentclass[12pt]{article}
\usepackage[utf8]{inputenc}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{amsfonts}
\usepackage{amssymb}
\usepackage[left=1.5in, right=1.5in, top=1in, bottom=1in]{geometry}

\usepackage{enumitem}

\begin{document}

\title{Title}
\author{Author}
\date{\today}
\maketitle

\section{Section}

\begin{itemize}[itemsep=10pt]
\item Item 1
\item Item 2
\item Item 3
\end{itemize}

\end{document}
```

The `enumitem` package was loaded to allow the optional argument for `itemize`; the package also provides a simple way to change the layout for all lists in the document, if needed.

